                                    "bbox": [
                                        1282,
                                        805,
                                        2272,
                                        1448
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Fisheye- image and camera- parameter generation. For a fair comparison with the state- of- the- art method [53] in the estimation of tilt and roll angles, we used the generic camera model [53] to generate fisheye images. Following the procedure for dataset generation and capture [53], we generated fisheye images from panoramic images using the generic camera models with the ground- truth camera parameters in Table 4, and we captured outdoor images in Kyoto, Japan, using six off- the- shelf fisheye cameras. To generate the test set, we replaced the mixed and varying distributions in the training sets with a uniform distribution. Therefore, our generated fisheye images and ground- truth camera parameters were used for training and evaluation."
